        <relatedmaterial id="ref10">
            <head>Related Materials</head>
            <p>Additional Kenneth M. Swezey correspondence, publications, and research notes, as well as Nicola Tesla photographs, are held at the Smithsonian Institution's National Museum of American History. See the Museum Archive Center's website (
                <extref ns2:actuate="onLoad" ns2:show="new" ns2:href="http://americanhistory.si.edu/archives/d8047.htm">http://americanhistory.si.edu/archives/d8047.htm</extref>) for a description of the Kenneth M. Swezey papers held at the Museum.</p>
        </relatedmaterial>
        <scopecontent id="ref2">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The Kenneth M. Swezey papers include Swezey's personal papers, correspondence, published and unpublished writings, printed materials, books, photographs, slides, and travel artifacts. In addition to Swezey, the collection relates to Swezey's childhood and lifelong friend, Robert MacCrate, a New York City lawyer, and the Serbian inventor Nikola Tesla, with whom Swezey worked for a time.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <accessrestrict id="ref1">
